  "market_context": "GBP/USD on August 7, 2023, with a bullish 4-hour bias supported by an order block. Previous 4-hour high marked as draw on liquidity. Price expected to expand higher following an open-low-high-close delivery sequence across multiple time frames.",
  "key_observation": "After identifying the 4-hour draw on liquidity, price on the 1-minute formed an order block with a fair value gap above, offering a low-risk buy entry targeting the previous 4-hour high for 2R+ reward.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the 4-hour chart, identify the previous 4-hour high as the draw on liquidity, expecting bullish expansion supported by an order block.",
    "Step 2: Drop to the 15-minute chart, mark the new 4-hour candle open, and expect an open-low-high-close sequence — price should move down first before expanding higher.",
    "Step 3: Mark the 15-minute swing point; price sweeps it but closes back inside the range, confirming bullish intent toward the previous high.",
    "Step 4: Drop to the 1-minute chart at the new 15-minute candle open; watch for failure to displace below a swing point as a bullish signal.",
    "Step 5: Price prints a full-body candle into the prior low, generating displacement out and leaving an order block with a fair value gap above.",
    "Step 6: Identify the order block + FVG as a low-risk buy entry zone, with partials at the 1-minute high and final target at the previous 4-hour high (drawn liquidity).",
    "Step 7: Confirm reaction — price displaces upward, disrespects a bearish FVG by closing through it, and continues expanding toward the 4-hour drawn liquidity."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade plays out as anticipated — price reaches the previous 4-hour high before the 4-hour candle close, validating the low-risk buy entry with 2R+ achieved.",
  "lessons": "Top-down alignment from 4-hour bias to 1-minute execution, combined with an order block and FVG at a discount to the higher-time-frame open, produces low-risk, high-probability entries targeting HTF draw on liquidity.",
